# Tatiana Rosá – Academic Website (Static)

This folder contains a simple, professional academic website ready for **GitHub Pages**.

## Publish on GitHub Pages (5 steps)
1. Create a new repo on GitHub, e.g. `tatianarosa.github.io` (or any name).
2. Upload all the files in this folder to the repo (drag & drop).
3. If the repo is _not_ named `tatianarosa.github.io`, go to **Settings → Pages** and set:
   - **Source**: Deploy from a branch
   - **Branch**: `main` (root)
4. Wait ~1–2 minutes. Your site will be live at either:
   - `https://<your-username>.github.io/` (if the repo is that name), or
   - `https://<your-username>.github.io/<repo-name>/`
5. Update links in `cv.html` and `research.html` to your actual Dropbox/NBER PDF URLs (or host the PDFs in this repo under `/files/`).

## Editing
- Change text in the HTML files as needed.
- Styles live in `styles.css`.

